-- Nerd Standard Library (NSL)
--
-- Copyright (c) 2026 Matt Davies
--
-- Loads PNG and baseline JPEG images from bytes already available in memory.
-- The library does not read files directly; callers should provide bytes from
-- `@embed`, a future filesystem module, or another byte source.
--
-- Typical use is to import `std.image`, get a byte slice with `@embed`, pass it
-- to `Image.load_bytes(bytes, desired_channels)`, handle the returned
-- `Result[Image, ImageError]`, and `defer image.free()` after a successful
-- decode.
--
-- `desired_channels` can be `0` to preserve the source channel count, or `1`,
-- `2`, `3`, or `4` to request greyscale, greyscale-alpha, RGB, or RGBA output.
-- Decoded pixel bytes are owned by the returned `Image` and must be released
-- with `image.free()`.
